,Recommended,402300,18537175,"Posted: 17 October, 2015",all,Melanc,"TL, DR: This is a mix of SimTower and Unholy Heights. Breeding, building and the slow accumulation of power and resources. If you enjoyed one or both of the above games, you should give this a try.This game plays like SimTower, you gradually accumulate more resources and build to expand your domain. In exchange for a simpler building system, this game adds complexity in the form of monsters that you need to nurture and cross breed to evolve ever stronger monsters. The gameplay is surprisingly addictive; I'm writing this at 2am in the morning after a ""short"" session became 2 hours. Although there are no graphics, the user interface is functional and the status of your dungeon is clearly presented. I think this game is worth its asking price if you're looking for a game that has the intensity of an RTS, the atmosphere of Dungeon Keeper, and easily-understood game mechanics."
